		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="456">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I want to thank John Frank for his essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4692">Pioneers</a>&rdquo; [August 2012], about a relationship falling apart during the onset of mental illness. His description of the stages preceding full-blown mania were very like my own experience. Two moments moved me most: the scene in which Teresa breaks up with Frank because he is &ldquo;too intense&rdquo; (I&rsquo;ve been hearing those words since I was a teenager); and the two beautiful last paragraphs about the psych ward, where Frank comes to understand why his father and other sufferers of depression sleep on the couch instead of the bed &mdash; they want to be a part of things. This feeling, too, I know well.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Dana Greci<br>Fairbanks, Alaska</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

